	<section class="article-content clearfix" itemprop="articleBody">
		<p>Persivia’s Medication Management Solution enables clinicians to obtain critical real-time information, such as clinical parameters, lab values and therapeutic levels, which are especially important for high-risk medications such as Heparin, Warfarin and Insulin. <br /><br />Persivia’s technology provides real-time recommendations and analytics dashboards to end users, notifying them of several important patient status updates, such as culture and sensitivity results, number of days a patient has been on antimicrobial therapy, and specific broad and narrow spectrum medications to administer per facility guidelines and practices. These real-time data recommendations are used to optimize treatment and improve outcomes.</p>
<h4>Persivia’s Medication Management Solution Includes:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Medication Monitoring: IV-to-PO conversion, renal and hepatic dosing, and antibiotic de-escalation</li>
<li>Patient Safety: Adverse Drug Reaction (ADR) &amp; Adverse Event (AE) avoidance</li>
<li>Antimicrobial Stewardship: Sensitive and resistant drug/bug combinations, antibiotic streamlining, real-time antibiograms</li>
<li>Identify Multi-drug Resistant Organism (MDRO): Advise clinicians on appropriate isolation procedures based on the disease or condition of the patient</li>
<li>Maximize Time &amp; Resources: Single sign-on, ease-of-use and customized reporting options allow clinicians to configure reports to meet their specific needs.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Persivia is the Medication Management Solution to:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Provide Alerts on Drug/Bug Mismatch</li>
<li>Monitor Peak and Trough</li>
<li>Identify Potential Adverse Events</li>
</ul>	</section>
	
